 Hard by a great forest dwelt a poor wood-cutter with his wife and his
 two children. The boy was called Hansel and the girl Gretel. He had l
ittle to bite and to break, and once when great dearth fell on the lan
d, he could no longer procure even daily bread.Now when he thought ove
r this by night in his bed, and tossed about in his anxiety, he groane
